<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<!-- hamlive-oss — MIT License. See LICENSE. -->

<head>
  <%- include('./partials/head') %> <%- include('./partials/pageTopFeatures') %>

  <title><%= server.appName %> - Homepage <%if (server.logLevel !== "info") {%> (<%= server.logLevel %>) <%}%></title>
    </head>

    <body class="bg-dark text-light">
        <%- include('./partials/navbar', {user: user}) %>

    <div class="container static-page">
      <div class="row">
        <div class="col p-md-2 m-md-3">
          <ul class="nav nav-tabs">
            <li class="nav-item">
              <a class="nav-link" href="/views/dashboard">Live Nets</a>
            </li>
            <li class="nav-item">
              <a class="nav-link" href="/intro">How-To Video</a>
            </li>
            <li class="nav-item">
              <a class="nav-link active bg-secondary" href="#">Google Auth Homepage</a>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="d-flex container mt-4 h5">
      <div class="flex-fill d-flex justify-content-center">
        <strong>Google oAuth2 Homepage</strong>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="d-flex container">
      <div class="flex-fill p-2 mt-4">
        <p>
          <u>Accurately Represent your app's identity:</u>
          The <%= server.appName %> App is
          <a href="/"><%= server.appName %></a>
          . <%= server.appName %> is built to facilitate on-the-air meetups of amateur radio operators. In ham radio
          jargon, such meet-ups are referred to as 'nets'. <%= server.appName %> aims to support the amateur radio hobby
          and bolster ham radio's usage by making the starting and attendance of nets as easy as possible.
        </p>
        <p>
          <u>What will this app do with user data?:</u>
          The only user data received is: name, email and profile picture. Name and profile picture will be
          displayed when you attend a net online or over-the air. Email is used only in the event a user
          follows a net, in order to receive notification when a net is about to start.
        </p>
        <p>
          <u>How does this app enhance user functionality?:</u>
          This app provides rich ancillary information for active amateur radio nets. Users can not only see
          other net attendees (which they may not be able to hear over-the-air, depending on conditions), they
          can interaction with each other by providing signal reports and raising/lowering their hands.
          Additionally, an interactive chat widget allows for real-time communication between net attendees.
        </p>
        <p>
          Link to Privacy Policy:
          <a href="/views/privacypolicy">Click here.</a>
        </p>
        <p>
          <u>Describe the content, context, or connection to the app:</u>
          The <%= server.appName %> App is this website, which provides a series of tools to aid amateur (ham) radio
          operators in their hobby. It provides a series of tools to allow users to be aware when nets (on-air
          meet-ups) are occurring and to interact in said nets.
        </p>
        <p>
          <u>How does this application access, use, store, or share Google user data?:</u>
          The only Google user data received is: name, email and profile picture. These are accessed via
          OAuth2 login. These are stored in a database and used to display to users during net attendance.
          Email address is never shared with others and only used if a user opts-in to receive email
          notifications of a net starting. More detail is available in the
          <a href="/views/privacypolicy">Privacy Policy</a>
          .
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <%- include('./partials/pageBottomFeatures') %>

    <script src="/js/byView/<%= VIEW %>/main.js" type="module"></script>
    </body>
    <%- include('./partials/footer') %>

</html>